{
  "id": 132987,
  "referenceId": 109041,
  "name": "James 2:1–13",
  "localizedName": "James 2:1–13",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "James made it clear that Jesus’ followers are to treat all people with respect. They mustn’t favour one person over another."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "James gave an example of how rich people and poor people were treated in his time. The royal law that James talked about is from the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108192",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Old Testament"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". It’s the most important commandment in the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108335",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Law of Moses"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " about how to treat others. It taught people to love their "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108370",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "neighbours"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " as they loved themselves."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus showed how this included showing "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108342",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "mercy"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " to others. He told a story about that in Matthew 18:21–35."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus’ followers won’t be judged based on the Law of Moses. They will be judged based on the law that gives freedom. James meant that believers will be judged according to God’s mercy. So they must treat others with mercy as well."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
